fields.title: Chicken Curry
fields.ingredients: chicken, onion, garlic, tomato, curry powder, oil
fields.instructions: Heat oil in a large skillet. Add chopped onions and cook until golden. Add garlic and tomatoes, cook until soft. Add curry powder and chicken. Cook until done. Garnish and serve.

fields.title: Grilled Chicken
fields.ingredients: chicken breast, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, herbs, salt, pepper
fields.instructions: Marinate chicken with olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, and herbs for 1 hour. Grill until cooked. Serve hot.

fields.title: Chicken Alfredo Pasta
fields.ingredients: chicken breast, fettuccine, heavy cream, garlic, parmesan cheese, butter
fields.instructions: Cook pasta. Saut� chicken until done. Prepare sauce with cream, garlic, butter, and cheese. Combine and serve.

fields.title: Chicken Salad
fields.ingredients: chicken breast, mixed greens, tomatoes, cucumber, olive oil, lemon juice
fields.instructions: Grill chicken and slice. Toss veggies with olive oil and lemon juice. Top with chicken.

fields.title: Chicken Stir Fry
fields.ingredients: chicken, bell peppers, soy sauce, garlic, ginger, oil
fields.instructions: Stir fry chicken with garlic and ginger. Add peppers and soy sauce. Cook until tender. Serve with rice.

fields.title: Chicken Tacos
fields.ingredients: chicken, taco shells, lettuce, tomato, cheese, salsa
fields.instructions: Cook and shred chicken. Fill taco shells with chicken and toppings. Serve immediately.

fields.title: Chicken Soup
fields.ingredients: chicken, carrots, celery, onion, garlic, broth, noodles
fields.instructions: Boil chicken and veggies in broth. Add noodles and cook until tender. Season and serve.

fields.title: Chicken Sandwich
fields.ingredients: chicken breast, bread, lettuce, tomato, mayo, cheese
fields.instructions: Cook chicken breast. Assemble sandwich with bread and toppings. Serve chilled or warm.

fields.title: Buffalo Chicken Wings
fields.ingredients: chicken wings, hot sauce, butter, garlic powder, salt
fields.instructions: Bake or fry wings. Toss in hot sauce mixed with melted butter and garlic powder. Serve with dip.

fields.title: Chicken Fried Rice
fields.ingredients: chicken, rice, eggs, peas, soy sauce, green onions, oil
fields.instructions: Cook chicken and scramble eggs. Stir fry rice, peas, chicken, and eggs with soy sauce. Garnish with green onions.

fields.title: Chicken Fry
fields.ingredients: chicken, ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, garam masala, black pepper powder, lemon juice, salt, oil, curry leaves (optional), fresh coriander leaves (optional)
fields.instructions: Marinate the chicken with ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric, coriander powder, lemon juice, and salt. Heat oil in a pan. Fry the marinated chicken pieces until golden brown and cooked through. Add garam masala and black pepper powder towards the end. Garnish with curry leaves and fresh coriander leaves if desired. Serve hot.

fields.title: Chicken Kebab
fields.ingredients: chicken mince, ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, garam masala, coriander powder, salt, lemon juice, fresh coriander, oil
fields.instructions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small patties or skewers. Grill or shallow fry until cooked and golden brown. Serve hot with mint chutney.

fields.title: Chicken Wings
fields.ingredients: chicken wings, ginger garlic paste, soy sauce, chili sauce, honey, black pepper, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Marinate chicken wings with ginger garlic paste, soy sauce, chili sauce, honey, salt, and pepper for 1 hour. Bake or deep fry until crispy and cooked through. Serve hot.

fields.title: Chicken 65
fields.ingredients: chicken, ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, curry leaves, yogurt, cornflour, salt, oil, lemon juice
fields.instructions: Marinate chicken with ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric, yogurt, cornflour, and salt. Deep fry until crispy. In a separate pan, heat oil, add curry leaves and fried chicken, toss well. Add lemon juice and serve hot.

fields.title: Chicken Tandoori
fields.ingredients: chicken, yogurt, ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, garam masala, lemon juice, salt, oil, mustard seeds (optional), coriander leaves (optional)
fields.instructions: Marinate chicken with yogurt, ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric, garam masala, lemon juice, salt, and oil. Let it rest for at least 2 hours or overnight. Grill or bake at high heat until cooked and slightly charred. Garnish with coriander leaves and serve with lemon wedges.

fields.title: Egg Fried Rice
fields.ingredients: eggs, cooked rice, peas, carrots, soy sauce, green onions, oil
fields.instructions: Scramble eggs in hot oil and set aside. Stir fry peas and carrots, add cooked rice and soy sauce. Mix in scrambled eggs and green onions. Cook for 2-3 minutes and serve hot.

fields.title: Deviled Eggs
fields.ingredients: boiled eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, paprika, salt, pepper
fields.instructions: Cut boiled eggs in half, remove yolks. Mix yolks with mayonnaise, mustard, salt, and pepper. Fill egg whites with yolk mixture. Sprinkle paprika and serve chilled.

fields.title: Egg Salad Sandwich
fields.ingredients: boiled eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, celery, salt, pepper, bread
fields.instructions: Chop boiled eggs and mix with mayonnaise, mustard, chopped celery, salt, and pepper. Spread on bread slices and assemble sandwich. Serve chilled.

fields.title: Spanish Tortilla
fields.ingredients: eggs, potatoes, onion, olive oil, salt
fields.instructions: Thinly slice potatoes and onions. Fry in olive oil until tender. Beat eggs with salt and mix with potatoes and onions. Pour mixture into pan and cook until set. Flip to cook other side. Serve warm.

fields.title: Egg Bhurji (Indian Scrambled Eggs)
fields.ingredients: eggs, onion, tomato, green chili, turmeric, coriander powder, oil, salt, fresh coriander
fields.instructions: Heat oil, saut� onions and chili until soft. Add tomatoes and spices. Pour beaten eggs and scramble until cooked. Garnish with coriander and serve with bread or roti.

fields.title: Egg Drop Soup
fields.ingredients: eggs, chicken broth, cornstarch, green onions, soy sauce, salt, pepper
fields.instructions: Boil chicken broth and thicken with cornstarch. Slowly pour beaten eggs into hot broth while stirring to create egg ribbons. Add soy sauce, salt, pepper, and garnish with green onions. Serve hot.

fields.title: Shakshuka
fields.ingredients: eggs, tomatoes, onion, garlic, bell pepper, paprika, cumin, olive oil, salt, pepper
fields.instructions: Saut� onion, garlic, and bell pepper in olive oil. Add tomatoes and spices, cook until sauce thickens. Crack eggs into sauce, cover and cook until eggs are set. Serve with bread.

fields.title: Fish Fried Rice
fields.ingredients: fish (cooked or fillets), cooked rice, peas, carrots, soy sauce, green onions, oil
fields.instructions: Cook fish and flake it. Stir fry peas and carrots in hot oil. Add cooked rice and soy sauce, mix well. Add flaked fish and green onions, cook for 2-3 minutes. Serve hot.

fields.title: Fish Deviled Eggs
fields.ingredients: boiled eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, paprika, salt, pepper, cooked fish flakes
fields.instructions: Cut boiled eggs in half, remove yolks. Mix yolks with mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, and cooked fish flakes. Fill egg whites with mixture. Sprinkle paprika and serve chilled.

fields.title: Fish Salad Sandwich
fields.ingredients: boiled eggs, cooked fish flakes, mayonnaise, mustard, celery, salt, pepper, bread
fields.instructions: Chop boiled eggs and mix with cooked fish flakes, mayonnaise, mustard, chopped celery, salt, and pepper. Spread on bread slices and assemble sandwich. Serve chilled.

fields.title: Spanish Fish Tortilla
fields.ingredients: eggs, potatoes, onion, cooked fish flakes, olive oil, salt
fields.instructions: Thinly slice potatoes and onions. Fry in olive oil until tender. Beat eggs with salt and mix with potatoes, onions, and cooked fish flakes. Pour mixture into pan and cook until set. Flip to cook other side. Serve warm.

fields.title: Fish Bhurji (Indian Style Scrambled Fish)
fields.ingredients: eggs, cooked fish flakes, onion, tomato, green chili, turmeric, coriander powder, oil, salt, fresh coriander
fields.instructions: Heat oil, saut� onions and chili until soft. Add tomatoes and spices. Add cooked fish flakes and pour beaten eggs, scramble until cooked. Garnish with coriander and serve with bread or roti.

fields.title: Fish Egg Drop Soup
fields.ingredients: eggs, fish broth (or chicken broth with fish flavor), cornstarch, green onions, soy sauce, salt, pepper
fields.instructions: Boil fish broth and thicken with cornstarch. Slowly pour beaten eggs into hot broth while stirring to create egg ribbons. Add soy sauce, salt, pepper, and garnish with green onions. Serve hot.

fields.title: Fish Shakshuka
fields.ingredients: eggs, tomatoes, onion, garlic, bell pepper, paprika, cumin, cooked fish flakes, olive oil, salt, pepper
fields.instructions: Saut� onion, garlic, and bell pepper in olive oil. Add tomatoes and spices, cook until sauce thickens. Add cooked fish flakes. Crack eggs into sauce, cover and cook until eggs are set. Serve with bread.

fields.title: Masala Dosa
fields.ingredients: rice, urad dal, potato, mustard seeds, curry leaves, green chilies, turmeric, oil, salt
fields.instructions: Soak and grind rice and urad dal to make dosa batter; ferment overnight. Prepare potato masala by saut�ing mustard seeds, curry leaves, chilies, and boiled potatoes with turmeric and salt. Spread batter thin on hot griddle, cook till crisp, fill with potato masala, fold and serve with chutney and sambar.

fields.title: Poha (Flattened Rice)
fields.ingredients: poha (flattened rice), mustard seeds, green chili, curry leaves, turmeric, peanuts, onions, lemon, coriander, oil, salt
fields.instructions: Rinse poha lightly. Heat oil, add mustard seeds, peanuts, chilies, curry leaves, and onions. Saut�, add turmeric and salt. Add poha, mix gently and cook for 2-3 minutes. Garnish with lemon juice and coriander leaves. Serve hot.

fields.title: Idli with Coconut Chutney
fields.ingredients: rice, urad dal, fenugreek seeds, grated coconut, green chili, mustard seeds, curry leaves, oil, salt
fields.instructions: Soak rice, urad dal, and fenugreek seeds; grind separately and ferment overnight to make batter. Steam batter in idli molds for 10-12 minutes. Prepare chutney by grinding coconut, chili, salt, and tempering mustard seeds and curry leaves. Serve idlis hot with chutney and sambar.

fields.title: Aloo Paratha
fields.ingredients: wheat flour, boiled potatoes, green chili, coriander, garam masala, salt, butter, oil
fields.instructions: Prepare dough with wheat flour and water. Mash potatoes and mix with chopped chilies, coriander, garam masala, and salt. Roll dough into balls, stuff with potato filling, roll again, and cook on hot griddle with butter/oil until golden brown. Serve hot with yogurt or pickle.

fields.title: Upma
fields.ingredients: semolina (rava), mustard seeds, green chilies, ginger, curry leaves, mustard seeds, urad dal, chana dal, onion, cashews, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Roast semolina till fragrant. Heat oil, add mustard seeds, urad dal, chana dal, chilies, ginger, onions, and curry leaves. Add water and salt, bring to boil. Slowly add semolina, stirring continuously to avoid lumps. Cook till water is absorbed and upma is soft. Garnish with cashews and serve hot.

fields.title: Medu Vada
fields.ingredients: urad dal, green chili, ginger, curry leaves, black pepper, salt, oil for frying
fields.instructions: Soak urad dal, grind to a smooth batter. Add chopped green chili, ginger, curry leaves, black pepper, and salt. Shape batter into doughnut shapes and deep fry in hot oil till golden and crisp. Serve with sambar and coconut chutney.

fields.title: Besan Chilla (Savory Chickpea Pancake)
fields.ingredients: gram flour (besan), chopped onions, green chili, coriander leaves, turmeric, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Mix besan with water to make a batter. Add onions, chili, coriander, turmeric, and salt. Heat a griddle, pour batter and spread thin. Cook both sides till golden. Serve hot with chutney or yogurt.

fields.title: Pongal
fields.ingredients: rice, moong dal, ginger, black pepper, cumin seeds, curry leaves, cashews, ghee, salt
fields.instructions: Roast moong dal, cook with rice and water till soft. In a pan, heat ghee, add mustard seeds, cumin seeds, pepper, ginger, curry leaves, and cashews. Pour seasoning into cooked rice mixture, mix well and serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar.

fields.title: Samosa
fields.ingredients: all-purpose flour, boiled potatoes, green peas, green chili, ginger, cumin seeds, garam masala, coriander, salt, oil for frying
fields.instructions: Make a stiff dough using flour and water. For filling, saut� cumin seeds, green chili, ginger; add boiled potatoes, peas, garam masala, coriander, and salt. Roll dough thin, cut into cones, stuff with filling, seal edges. Deep fry in hot oil until golden and crisp. Serve with chutney.

fields.title: Bajji (Vegetable Fritters)
fields.ingredients: gram flour (besan), rice flour, sliced vegetables (potato, onion, raw banana, chili), turmeric, red chili powder, salt, oil for frying
fields.instructions: Make a thick batter with besan, rice flour, turmeric, chili powder, and salt adding water gradually. Dip vegetable slices in batter and deep fry until golden and crispy. Serve hot with chutney or sauce.

fields.title: Paneer Pakora
fields.ingredients: paneer cubes, gram flour (besan), rice flour, carom seeds (ajwain), red chili powder, salt, water, oil for frying
fields.instructions: Prepare batter mixing besan, rice flour, ajwain, chili powder, salt, and water to a thick consistency. Dip paneer cubes in batter and deep fry till golden. Serve hot with green chutney or ketchup.

fields.title: Onion Bhaji
fields.ingredients: thinly sliced onions, gram flour (besan), cumin seeds, chopped green chili, coriander, salt, water, oil for frying
fields.instructions: Mix onions with besan, cumin seeds, green chili, coriander, salt, and enough water to form a thick batter. Drop spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until crisp and golden. Serve with chutney.

fields.title: Aloo Tikki
fields.ingredients: boiled potatoes, green chili, coriander, chaat masala, salt, bread crumbs, oil for frying
fields.instructions: Mash potatoes, add chopped chili, coriander, chaat masala, and salt. Shape into patties, coat with bread crumbs. Shallow fry till golden brown on both sides. Serve with tamarind chutney or yogurt.

fields.title: Pani Puri
fields.ingredients: semolina, all-purpose flour, tamarind, mint leaves, coriander leaves, green chilies, black salt, chaat masala, boiled potatoes, boiled chickpeas
fields.instructions: Make small hollow puris by deep frying dough made from semolina and flour. Prepare spicy tamarind-mint water (pani). Stuff puris with mashed potatoes and chickpeas, then fill with the flavored water. Serve immediately.

fields.title: Paneer Tikka
fields.ingredients: paneer cubes, yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric, garam masala, lemon juice, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Marinate paneer cubes in a mixture of yogurt and spices for 1-2 hours. Thread onto skewers and grill or bake until slightly charred. Serve hot with green chutney.

fields.title: Chili Paneer
fields.ingredients: paneer, cornflour, all-purpose flour, bell peppers, onions, green chilies, soy sauce, chili sauce, garlic, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Coat paneer cubes in a batter of cornflour and flour and deep fry. Stir-fry onions, peppers, garlic, and chilies. Add sauces and toss in fried paneer. Cook for a few minutes and serve hot.

fields.title: Bhakarwadi
fields.ingredients: gram flour, wheat flour, poppy seeds, sesame seeds, dry coconut, red chili powder, turmeric, jaggery, tamarind paste, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Make dough from flours and roll into thin circles. Prepare spicy-sweet filling with seeds, spices, jaggery, and tamarind. Spread filling, roll tightly, slice into rounds, and deep fry till crispy. Cool and store.

fields.title: Masala Peanuts
fields.ingredients: raw peanuts, gram flour, red chili powder, turmeric, chaat masala, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Mix peanuts with gram flour and spices to coat evenly. Deep fry in hot oil till crunchy and golden. Drain and cool before serving.

fields.title: Paneer Butter Masala
fields.ingredients: paneer, butter, cream, tomatoes, ginger-garlic paste, kasuri methi, garam masala, chili powder, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Cook tomato gravy with spices and butter. Add paneer cubes, cream, and kasuri methi. Simmer till well combined and serve hot with naan or roti.

fields.title: Palak Paneer
fields.ingredients: spinach, paneer, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, green chili, cumin seeds, garam masala, cream, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Blanch spinach and puree. Saut� onions, garlic, and ginger; add tomatoes and spices. Mix in spinach puree and paneer cubes. Cook for 5-10 minutes, add cream and serve hot.

fields.title: Aloo Gobi
fields.ingredients: potatoes, cauliflower, tomatoes, ginger, garlic, green chili, turmeric, cumin seeds, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Heat oil, saut� cumin seeds, ginger, garlic, and chili. Add potatoes and cauliflower, then tomatoes and spices. Cook covered till vegetables are tender. Garnish with coriander and serve hot.

fields.title: Baingan Bharta (Smoky Mashed Eggplant)
fields.ingredients: eggplants, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, green chili, mustard seeds, cumin seeds, coriander powder, turmeric, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Roast eggplants till charred. Peel and mash. Saut� mustard seeds, cumin, onion, garlic, and chili. Add tomatoes and spices. Mix in mashed eggplant, cook for few minutes and serve hot.

fields.title: Chana Masala
fields.ingredients: chickpeas, onion, tomato, ginger-garlic paste, cumin seeds, garam masala, chili powder, turmeric, coriander powder, amchur powder, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Saut� onions, ginger-garlic paste, and tomatoes with spices. Add boiled chickpeas and simmer till thick. Garnish with coriander and serve with rice or roti.

fields.title: Mixed Vegetable Curry
fields.ingredients: carrots, beans, peas, potatoes, tomatoes, onions, ginger, garlic, cumin seeds, turmeric, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Heat oil, saut� cumin seeds, ginger, garlic, and onions. Add chopped vegetables, tomatoes, and spices. Cook covered till vegetables are tender. Serve hot with roti or rice.

fields.title: Matar Paneer
fields.ingredients: paneer, green peas, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin seeds, turmeric, garam masala, chili powder, cream, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Saut� cumin seeds, onions, ginger, garlic, and tomatoes with spices. Add peas and paneer cubes. Cook till peas are tender. Add cream, simmer, and serve hot.

fields.title: Bhindi Masala (Okra Curry)
fields.ingredients: okra, onion, tomato, ginger, green chili, cumin seeds, turmeric, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Heat oil, saut� cumin seeds, onions, and green chili. Add chopped okra, tomatoes, and spices. Cook uncovered till okra is tender and dry. Serve with roti or rice.

fields.title: Aloo Matar
fields.ingredients: potatoes, green peas, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin seeds, turmeric, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil
fields.instructions: Saut� cumin seeds, onion, ginger, garlic, and tomatoes with spices. Add potatoes and peas, cook covered till tender. Serve hot with roti or rice.

fields.title: Gulab Jamun
fields.ingredients: milk powder, all-purpose flour, baking soda, ghee, milk, sugar, water, cardamom, rose water, saffron
fields.instructions: Make dough from milk powder, flour, baking soda, milk, and ghee. Shape into small balls. Deep fry until golden. Soak fried balls in warm sugar syrup flavored with cardamom, rose water, and saffron. Serve warm or cold.

fields.title: Rasgulla
fields.ingredients: milk, lemon juice, sugar, water, rose water, cardamom
fields.instructions: Boil milk and curdle with lemon juice to make chenna (paneer). Knead chenna into smooth balls. Boil in sugar syrup until they expand and become spongy. Add rose water and cardamom for flavor.

fields.title: Kheer (Rice Pudding)
fields.ingredients: basmati rice, milk, sugar, cardamom, saffron, almonds, pistachios, raisins
fields.instructions: Cook rice in milk on low heat until soft and thickened. Add sugar, cardamom, saffron, and nuts. Simmer for few minutes. Serve warm or chilled.

fields.title: Jalebi
fields.ingredients: all-purpose flour, yogurt, sugar, water, saffron, ghee or oil for frying
fields.instructions: Make a batter of flour and yogurt, ferment for a few hours. Deep fry in circular shapes in hot ghee. Soak fried jalebis in warm sugar syrup flavored with saffron. Serve crispy.

fields.title: Besan Ladoo
fields.ingredients: gram flour (besan), ghee, powdered sugar, cardamom, chopped nuts
fields.instructions: Roast besan in ghee on low flame till golden and aromatic. Remove from heat, add powdered sugar, cardamom, and nuts. Shape into round balls (ladoo) while warm.

fields.title: Sandesh
fields.ingredients: fresh paneer (chenna), sugar, cardamom, saffron, rose water
fields.instructions: Knead fresh paneer till smooth. Cook with sugar and cardamom on low heat till mixture thickens. Shape into decorative pieces. Garnish with saffron and rose water.

fields.title: Rabri
fields.ingredients: milk, sugar, cardamom, saffron, chopped nuts
fields.instructions: Boil milk on low heat, continuously stirring until it thickens and reduces. Add sugar, cardamom, saffron, and nuts. Serve chilled.

fields.title: Peda
fields.ingredients: khoya (reduced milk), sugar, cardamom, ghee, saffron, pistachios
fields.instructions: Cook khoya with sugar and cardamom till thick. Cool slightly, shape into small discs. Garnish with saffron strands and pistachios.

fields.title: Malpua
fields.ingredients: all-purpose flour, semolina, sugar, milk, fennel seeds, cardamom, oil for frying, sugar syrup
fields.instructions: Prepare batter with flour, semolina, sugar, milk, and spices. Deep fry in small pancakes. Soak briefly in sugar syrup and serve warm.

fields.title: prawns fry
fields.ingredients: prawns,oil,ginger garlic paste,water
fields.instructions: boil the oil and mix the prawns with oil and ginger garlic paste

fields.title: Prawn Curry (Indian Style)
fields.ingredients: prawns,onions,tomatoes,ginger garlic paste,turmeric,chill powder,coriander powder,garam masala,coconut milk,salt,onion,salt,oil
fields.instructions:
Saut� onions in oil until golden.

Add ginger-garlic paste and spices. Cook till fragrant.

Add tomatoes and cook until oil separates.

Add prawns and cook for 5�6 minutes. Add coconut milk if using.

Garnish with coriander and serve with rice or chapati.

fields.title: Spicy Prawn Fry (Andhra Style)
fields.ingredients: prawns,onions,green chilly,curry leaves,red chilli powder,turmeric,salt,oil
fields.instructions:
Heat oil, saut� onions and green chilies.

Add curry leaves and spices.

Add prawns and cook until dry and well coated (about 8 minutes).

Serve as a side with rice or as a starter.

fields.title: Vegetable Pulao
fields.ingredients: basmati rice,mixed vegetables,onions,salt,ghee,oil,Whole spices
fields.instructions:
Heat oil, saut� whole spices and onion till golden.

Add vegetables and saut� 2 mins.

Add rice, 2 cups water, and salt.

Cover and cook till rice is done (10�12 mins). Serve hot.

fields.title: Aloo Gobi
fields.ingredients: potato,cauliflower,tomato,onion,turmeric,red chilli,garam masala,salt,oil
fields.instructions:
Heat oil, add cumin, onion, and saut�.

Add tomato and spices. Cook till soft.

Add potatoes and cauliflower, little water, and cover to cook.

Garnish with coriander.

fields.title: Sweetcorn Soup
fields.ingredients: sweetcorn,onion,butter,oil,salt,pepper,allpurpose flour,water
fields.instructions: Heat butter or oil in a pot over medium heat. Add chopped onion and garlic, saut� until soft and translucent (about 3-4 minutes).Add the sweetcorn kernels to the pot and saut� for 2-3 minutes.Sprinkle the flour and stir well to coat the veggies (this will help thicken the soup).Pour in the vegetable broth and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.Use an immersion blender to puree the soup until smooth. (Alternatively, transfer in batches to a blender, then return to pot.)Stir in the milk and heat through. Do not boil after adding milk to prevent curdling.Add salt and pepper to taste.Ladle into bowls and garnish with chopped coriander or spring onions.

fields.title: Bread Jam
fields.ingredients: bread,jam,butter,fruits
fields.instructions: Lightly toast the bread slices if you prefer a crisp texture. You can skip this if you like it soft.Spread a thin layer of butter on each slice if you like a rich flavor.Take one tablespoon of jam and evenly spread it on one side of each bread slice.Place thin slices of banana, apple, or strawberries on top of the jam for a fruity twist.Place one slice on top of the other with the jam sides facing in.Cut the sandwich diagonally or into small squares for easy snacking.
